 <num>PR 325</num>

creation.value: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace <date>2018-12-10T21:33:44</date>

abstract.value:
Approximately 154 color and black-and-white photographs that comprised two exhibitions at the New-York Historical Society: <extref actuate="onRequest" href="https://www.nyhistory.org/exhibitions/%E2%80%9Ci-am-king-world%E2%80%9D-photographs-muhammad-ali-george-kalinsky">"I Am King of the World": Photographs of Muhammad Ali by George Kalinsky</extref>
 (2016-2017), and <extref actuate="onRequest" href="https://www.nyhistory.org/exhibitions/new-york-through-lens-george-kalinsky">"New York Through the Lens of George Kalinsky</extref> (2018), which focused on well-known sports figures and popular entertainers who appeared at Madison Square Garden, where Kalinsky has been official photographer since 1966.

p.value: Available by advance appointment only. To schedule an appointment, contact the Print Room Librarian at <emph render="bold">printroom@nyhistory.org</emph>. Photocopying undertaken by staff only. Limited to twenty exposures of stable, unbound material per day. (Researchers may not accrue unused copy amounts from previous days.)

This collection should be cited as the <emph render="bold">George Kalinsky Photographs, PR 325, Department of Prints, Photographs, and Architectural Collections, The New-York Historical Society</emph>.
For more information visit the photographer's website: <extref href="http://georgekalinsky.com/">georgekalinsky.com.</extref>
<emph render="boldunderline">Tennis</emph>: Roger Federer, Billie Jean King, John McEnroe, Juan Martín del Potro, Sloane Stephens, Serena Williams, Venus Williams

Series I. Images from "I Am King of the World": Photographs of Muhammad Ali by George Kalinsky1965-1999Scope and Contents

The 46 prints in Series I formed the exhibition "I Am King of the World": Photographs of Muhammad Ali by George Kalinsky, which ran at the New-York Historical Society from December 11, 2016 through March 26, 2017.

Arrangement

The photographs in Series I are matted and filed in numerical order to match their position on the exhibition checklist, a copy of which is filed in Box 1. Corresponding numbers were written on the back of each mat by the archivist. All prints measure 20 x 24 inches.

Images from "New York Through the Lens of George Kalinsky"1955, 1965-2017Scope and Contents

The bulk of the approximately 108 prints in Series II (i.e., all of the matted prints, numbered 1 through 72) formed the exhibition "New York Through the Lens of George Kalinsky", which ran at the New-York Historical Society from February 2 through September 30, 2018.

Series II includes a number of unmatted photographs that were printed for potential use in the exhibition, but were ultimately not included in the final checklist. These prints, along with some duplicates of those that were used in the exhibition, are stored in Box 8.

Arrangement

The photographs in Series II that appeared in the exhibition are matted and filed in numerical order to match their position on the exhibition checklist, a copy of which is filed in Box 4. Corresponding numbers were written on the back of each mat by the archivist.
